ggplot(df, aes(x = AgeGroup, fill = factor(HeartDisease))) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill") +  # 'fill' makes it a percentage within each bin
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("lightblue", "lightcoral"),

# Assuming eig is an object from eigen() function
eigenvalues <- eig$values

# Calculate percentage and cumulative percentage
percentage <- eigenvalues / sum(eigenvalues)
cumulative_percentage <- cumsum(percentage)

# Create component names dynamically based on the number of eigenvalues
variables <- paste0("Component ", seq_along(eigenvalues))

# Create result table
result_table <- data.frame(
  Variable = variables,
  Eigenvalue = round(eigenvalues, 4),
  Percentage = round(percentage * 100, 4),
  Cumulative_Percentage = round(cumulative_percentage * 100, 4)
)

# Print result table
print(result_table)
